OL,7,FIt also comes as analysts Cornwall
OL,8,FInsight revised up their previous
OL,9,Fforecast of a further 1% increase to
OL,10,Fthe price cap in April, now suggesting
OL,11,Fhouseholds will face an almost 3% hike.
OL,13,FOfgem has urged customers to take
OL,14,Fadvantage of increasing choice among
OL,15,Fsuppliers and look for the best deal
OL,16,Fto help keep their bills down, saying
OL,17,Fhouseholds could save up to #140.
OL,19,FThe price cap does not limit total
OL,20,Fbills, because householders still pay
OL,21,Ffor the amount of energy they consume.
